78
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:55,840
We celebrate Kepler, but we should also 
celebrate Brahe for his assiduous data  

79
00:06:55,840 --> 00:07:00,000
collection, which was ten times more 
precise than any previous observation. 

80
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:07,680
That extra decimal point of accuracy was 
essential for Kepler to get his results. 

81
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:15,360
He was using Euclidean geometry and the 
most advanced mathematics he could use at  

82
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:22,960
