96
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:40,240
He had some preconceived theories first.
It seems like this is less and less the  

97
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:48,480
way we make progress, just because the 
data is so much more massive and useful. 

98
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:54,880
Oh, interesting. I feel like the 20th-century 
science that you're describing actually very  

99
00:08:54,880 --> 00:09:01,120
well describes what happened with Kepler.
He did have these ideas—1595 and '96 is where  

100
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:06,720
he comes up with the polygons and then the 
