simulations, and now that you've got the data,  

104
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:28,000
you can keep trying random things.
If it wasn't for that, Kepler would be  

105
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:33,520
out there just writing books about harmonics 
and Platonic objects, and there would be  

106
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:39,600
nothing to actually verify against.
The data was extremely important. The  

107
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:44,720
distinction I was trying to make was that 
traditionally, you make a hypothesis and  

108
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:50,240
