353
00:32:11,520 --> 00:32:19,920
But it does seem like it was this one-off thing.
Maybe one analogy for these problems is  

354
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:26,400
that you're in some sort of mountain 
range with all kinds of cliffs and walls. 

355
00:32:27,120 --> 00:32:33,680
Maybe there's a little wall which is three 
feet high, and one that's six feet high,  

356
00:32:33,680 --> 00:32:38,080
and then there's fifteen feet high, and 
then there are some mile-high cliffs. 

357
00:32:39,120 --> 00:32:43,040
You're trying to climb as many of these 
cliffs as possible, but it's in the dark. 

358
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:46,080
We don't know which ones are 
tall, which ones are short. 

359
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:50,720
So we try to light some candles 
and make some maps, and slowly we  

360
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:56,080
figure out some of them are climbable.
Some of them we can identify a partial  

361
00:32:56,960 --> 00:33:02,240
track in the wall that you can reach first.
These AI tools, they're like jumping  

362
00:33:02,240 --> 00:33:06,960
machines that can jump two meters 
in the air, higher than any human. 

363
00:33:06,960 --> 00:33:09,440
Sometimes they jump in the wrong 
direction, and sometimes they crash,  

364
00:33:09,440 --> 00:33:18,800
but sometimes they can reach the tops of the 
lowest walls that we couldn't reach before. 

365
00:33:18,800 --> 00:33:22,000
We've just set them loose in this 
mountain range, hopping around. 

366
00:33:23,120 --> 00:33:28,560
There was this exciting period where they could 
