367
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:36,960
Maybe the next time there's a big 
advance in the models, they will  

368
00:33:36,960 --> 00:33:45,760
try it again, and a few more will be breached.
But it's a different style of doing mathematics. 

369
00:33:48,320 --> 00:33:54,640
Normally we would hill climb, make little 
markers, and try to identify partial things. 

370
00:33:56,560 --> 00:34:02,640
These tools either succeed or they fail.
They've been really bad at creating partial  

371
00:34:02,640 --> 00:34:08,400
progress or identifying intermediate 
